To clean a whiteboard, follow these steps:

1. Dry erase the surface: Use a whiteboard eraser or a soft cloth to remove any visible markings from the whiteboard. This will get rid of the majority of the dry erase marker ink.

2. Use whiteboard cleaner: Spray a whiteboard cleaner or a mixture of white vinegar and water (equal parts) onto the board. If you don't have whiteboard cleaner, you can use isopropyl alcohol (rubbing alcohol) or a window cleaner, but avoid any cleaner that contains harsh chemicals, as they may damage the whiteboard surface. Do a spot test of the cleaner in a small, inconspicuous area before a full application.
